{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Split Inbox View with Side-by-Side Pane Layout\n\nExtend the existing inbox view to support a split-pane layout that displays two inbox sections simultaneously, each filtered by smart labels or criteria, enabling rapid triage of incoming messages across multiple categories without context-switching.\n\n---\n\nBackground & Context\n\nThe inbox already supports a preview pane for reading individual messages. This feature builds on that foundation by allowing the inbox itself to be split into two parallel filtered lists — for example, \"Team\" on the left and \"Newsletters\" on the right — so users can compare, triage, and act on messages from distinct categories at a glance. Because the preview pane occupies horizontal space, it must become dismissible when split view is active.\n\n---\n\nRequirements\n\nLayout & Split View\n\n- Add a split view toggle control in the inbox toolbar (icon button or segmented control labeled \"Split View\")\n- When activated, divide the inbox horizontally into two equal-width panes, each rendering an independent email list\n- Each pane independently scrolls, selects, and loads messages\n- Persist the split view preference (enabled/disabled) in user settings so it survives navigation and page reloads\n- On viewports narrower than 1024px, gracefully degrade: either disable the toggle or stack panes vertically with a clear visual separator\n\nPreview Pane Behavior in Split View\n\n- When split view is active, add an explicit dismiss/hide control for the preview pane (e.g., a close icon or a \"Hide Preview\" button in the preview pane header)\n- Clicking a message in either pane opens the preview pane; dismissing it collapses it and restores full width to the two-column layout\n- The preview pane should open anchored to the pane whose message was selected (or span full width below both panes — define preferred behavior before implementation)\n- Ensure keyboard navigation (arrow keys, Escape to close preview) continues to work correctly across both panes\n\nSmart Labels / Inbox Sections\n\n- Allow each pane to be independently assigned an inbox section via a dropdown or label selector in the pane header\n- Support the following built-in criteria for sections: sender domain or address (e.g., \"Team\" = @company.com), label or tag (e.g., \"Newsletters\"), contact list membership (e.g., \"VIP Contacts\"), and unread-only toggle\n- Allow users to create, name, and save custom sections with one or more filter criteria (AND logic within a section)\n- Display the section name prominently in each pane header alongside the unread count for that section\n- Sections should filter in real time as new mail arrives via existing push notification infrastructure (Gmail Pub/Sub, Graph API webhooks)\n\nPane Management\n\n- Each pane header includes: section name/label, unread count badge, a section picker control, and (in split view) a swap-panes button to exchange left and right assignments\n- Provide a \"reset to defaults\" option that restores the two panes to their last saved or default section assignments\n- Allow users to save a named split layout (e.g., \"Work triage\") for quick recall\n\n---\n\nEdge Cases to Handle\n\n- Both panes assigned the same section: show a warning and allow it, but indicate duplication visually\n- A section that matches zero messages: show an empty state with the section name and a hint to adjust criteria\n- New message arrives that matches both pane filters: appears in both lists without duplication in the underlying data\n- Preview pane open when user toggles split view off: collapse preview gracefully and return to single-pane view\n- User resizes browser window mid-session: recalculate pane widths responsively without losing scroll position or selection state\n- Multi-account inbox: section criteria should be able to target a specific connected account or span all accounts\n\n---\n\nData & API Considerations\n\n- Add a user_inbox_sections table (or extend existing settings schema) to persist section definitions: id, user_id, name, filter_criteria (JSONB), created_at\n- Add a user_inbox_layout settings key to store the active split view state and pane-to-section assignments\n- Filtering should execute at the database query level (not client-side) to avoid loading irrelevant messages into memory — extend existing email list query to accept a section_id or inline filter payload\n- Reuse existing pgvector semantic search infrastructure where criteria include a semantic label (e.g., \"newsletters\" detected by embedding similarity rather than exact domain match)\n\n---\n\nAcceptance Criteria\n\n- User can enable split view and see two independently scrollable, filtered email lists side by side\n- Each pane can be assigned a different smart label/section independently\n- Preview pane has a visible dismiss control when split view is active and collapses without disrupting the split layout\n- Section definitions persist across sessions and reload correctly\n- Incoming mail routes into the correct pane section in real time without a manual refresh\n- All existing single-pane inbox functionality (search, compose, keyboard shortcuts, preview pane) continues to work correctly in both split and non-split modes",
